<p><q>Yes, mother,</q> she said, and mimed swinging an axe. As I put my socks and shoes on, she muttered, <q>They'll say, that Angela, she was such a good girl, who would have thought it, all the time she was in the back yard, helping her mother out by sharpening that hatchet.</q></p>

<p>I laughed. <q>You don't know how easy you have it. There is <i>no way</i> my folks would leave us alone in my bedroom until 11 o'clock.</q></p>

